        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>The Spring Suspension with Torque Rods is one of the less complicated suspensions available.
                </para>
                <para>Construction is simple, consisting of only two major components, leaf spring assemblies and torque
                    rods. As in any suspension, the leaf springs carry the axles. On a 6x4 chassis, the leaf spring
                    assemblies mount at three different locations on each side, distributing the load over a large area
                    of the frame rail (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300801">Figure 1</hotlnk>). On a 4x2 chassis, the leaf spring assemblies mount at
                    two locations (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0300802">Figure 2</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f0300801" figsize="pg-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg03/G0300801.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                             scalefitheight="392px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Spring Suspension with Torque Rods (6x4 Vehicles)</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. TORQUE ROD</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. SPRING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. CROSSMEMBER</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. EQUALIZER BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. SPRING BRACKET</callout1>
                        <callout1>6. SPRING ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                        <callout1>7. EQUALIZER</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0300802" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figg03/G0300802.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="232px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. Spring Suspension with Torque Rods (4x2 Vehicles)</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>Leaf spring assembly brackets and frame crossmembers are fastened to the frame rail with the same
                    hardware, resulting in the suspension being an integral part of the chassis.
                </para>
                <para>Torque rods provide stability by minimizing axle wind-up caused by driveline torque and the
                    resulting load transfer during braking.
                </para>
                <para>Suspension alignment is accomplished by inserting shims at the torque rod end mounting. Refer to
                    GROUP 03 - SPRING SUSPENSION ALIGNMENT in the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
